history.text: Hello!
Hello. Are you familiar with Superhero?
Yes, with both Marvel and DC.
Sorry I meant the movie named Batman Begins
Yes, I've seen the whole trilogy.  This was the best one, in my opinion.
I don't remember if I saw it. It's a 2006 movie.
Christian Bale is a good actor
2005, yes.   It relaunched the Batman movies after the mess that was Batman and Robin in '97.
I agree, he's the main reason this worked so well.
Looking at the reviews, rotten tomatoes gives it 84% 7.7/10
Do you like other types of movies too?
I think that's low!  The second one got more interest because of Heath Ledger's death, but this one set the bar really high.
Yes, although I'm big on Sci-Fi, I like comedies even more.
What do you like to watch?
Oh yea, I forgot about Heath Ledger. Sad.
I like good quality thrillers, drama
What type?  Would the Bourne movies be something you'd watch?
I've watched some of them. Yes. I think I did see this movie. I remember the cast in this one.  shows Michael Caine, Liam Neeson  Katie Holmes
Yes, that's the one.
The main villain is Ra's Al Ghul, who I think is Batman's best villain.
I remember the old Batman and Robin on television. Funny to think back on it.
Oh, my.  Yeah, those were interesting.  Did you ever see the old movie with the TV actors?  From 1966!
Yes, and the music still makes me laugh.
Got to admit, that version of Bat car was awesome!
Like the old King Kong versus newer movies. What a difference.
That's a good analogy.
I remember the old claymation technique on the original King Kong.  To a young child, it was amazing.

I'll bet it was! 
Ever heard of director Christopher Nolan? He's the one from this Batman movie.
Yes, among other things.  He's built quite a name for himself in Hollywood.
I'm not familiar with the name.
Look in imdb.com, He directed Memento and Inception as well.
Yea, I will. Since this movie was made in 2005, it's considered old by now, wouldn't think?
Probably.  Also, especially since it's the first of a trilogy and now Ben Affleck has taken over in several movies.  People nowadays think of him before Bale.
I think of Bale from that fighting movie. Affleck I always think of Matt Damon.
Yes, Damon and Affleck will always be associated with each other.  Not a bad thing, I guess.
They've both made some good movies. I can't think of anything else about Batman Begins,
I remember the fight scenes, and how Liam Neeson's character used a decoy to keep his identity hidden.

uid1response.feedback: I'm sure I've watched the movie, but I don't think I liked it.
